<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-08"><hi rend="italic">June 8,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>More railway destroyed. Protecting troops withdrawn. Chinese Government
                            becoming more helpless every day. Foreign troops will have to protect
                            railways. Russian, English, and Japanese are ready to do so. Twenty-four
                            foreign war vessels are at Taku. The United States has only one.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Conger.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>